definitions.definition: Used to indicate location, inclusion, or position within spatial, temporal or abstract limits.

examples: The dog is in the kennel.
There were three pickles in a jar.

subdefinitions.definition: Within the bounds or limits of.
examples: I like living in the city.
There are lots of trees in the park.
He sat in the chair.
She stood in the spotlight.
We are in the enemy camp.
Her plane is in the air.
Waiter! There's a fly in my soup!
There wasn't much of interest in her speech.
He hasn't got an original idea in him.

subdefinitions.definition: Part of; a member of; out of; from among.
examples: You are one in a million.
She's in an orchestra.
My birthday is in the first week of December.
Easter falls in the fourth lunar month.
The country reached a high level of prosperity in his first term.

subdefinitions.definition: Within (a certain elapsed time); by the end of.
examples: Will you be able to finish this in a week?
The massacre resulted in over 1000 deaths in three hours.

subdefinitions.definition: At the end of (a period of time ).
examples: They said they would call us in a week.
Many English nouns in -is form their plurals in -es , while those in kn- are pronounced just /n/-.
-is
-es
kn-
Less water gets in your boots this way.
She stood there looking in the window longingly.

definitions.definition: By (doing something); indicating action causing an effect or achieving a purpose .
examples: In replacing the faucet washers, he felt he was making his contribution to the environment.
In trying to make amends, she actually made matters worse.
My aim in travelling there was to find my missing friend.
My fat rolls around in folds.
The planes flew over in waves.
Arrange the chairs in a circle.

definitions.definition: Denoting a state of the subject.
examples: He stalked away in anger.
John is in a coma.
My fruit trees are in bud.
The company is in profit.

definitions.definition: Indicates, connotatively, a place-like form of someone's (or something's) personality, as his, her or its psychic and physical characteristics.
examples: You've got a friend in me.
He's met his match in her.
There has been no change in his condition.
What grade did he get in English?

definitions.definition: Used to indicate means, medium, format, genre, or instrumentality.

subdefinitions.definition: In the form of, in the denomination of.
examples: Please pay me in cash — preferably in tens and twenties.
The deposit can be in any legal tender, even in gold.
labels: of something offered or given in an exchange
subdefinitions.label_groups: of something offered or given in an exchange

subdefinitions.definition: Used to indicate a language, script, tone, etc. of a text, speech, etc.
examples: Beethoven's "Symphony No. 5" in C minor is among his most popular.
His speech was in French, but was simultaneously translated into eight languages.
When you write in cursive, it's illegible.
Military letters should be formal in tone, but not stilted.
